The paper discusses a redesign of ImageJ to support modern scientific imaging paradigms, which involves handling large, N-dimensional datasets and integrating with external applications. This suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques for image analysis, as well as deep learning (cs.DL) for handling large datasets. The paper also mentions a new plugin framework for extending functionality, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) or information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
